article.headline: SE Louisiana 71, Troy 68
article.story: HAMMOND, La. (AP) -- Daryl Cohen scored 18 points and Ricky Woods had a double-double of 13 points and 10 rebounds to lead Southeastern Louisiana to a 71-68 victory over Troy Saturday. Quenell Green added another 13 points for the Lions (1-1) and Chris Lee had 11 and dished out six assists. Sammy Sharp led Troy (2-2) with 15 points and grabbed nine rebounds. Bobby Dixon added 12 points and dished out eight assists. The Lions' bench that determined the difference as they outscored Troy, 34-16. Cohen, who did not play in last week's season-opening loss to nationally-ranked Texas Wesleyan, went 6-for-11 from the field and 5 of 10 from behind the 3-point line in 23 minutes off the bench.
